channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Responsible Visual Editing
item.description: To mitigate the negative implications of harmful images on research, we create a transparent and public dataset, AltBear, which expresses harmful information using teddy bears instead of humans.

item.title: Interpreting Themes from Educational Stories
item.description: Reading comprehension continues to be a crucial research focus in the NLP community.

item.title: PromptAD: Learning Prompts with only Normal Samples for Few-Shot Anomaly Detection
item.description: The vision-language model has brought great improvement to few-shot industrial anomaly detection, which usually needs to design of hundreds of prompts through prompt engineering.

item.title: RoT: Enhancing Large Language Models with Reflection on Search Trees
item.description: It uses a strong LLM to summarize guidelines from previous tree search experiences to enhance the ability of a weak LLM.

item.title: Normalizing Flows on the Product Space of SO(3) Manifolds for Probabilistic Human Pose Modeling
item.description: Normalizing flows have proven their efficacy for density estimation in Euclidean space, but their application to rotational representations, crucial in various domains such as robotics or human pose modeling, remains underexplored.

item.title: T-DEED: Temporal-Discriminability Enhancer Encoder-Decoder for Precise Event Spotting in Sports Videos
item.description: In this paper, we introduce T-DEED, a Temporal-Discriminability Enhancer Encoder-Decoder for Precise Event Spotting in sports videos.

item.title: Cell-Free Multi-User MIMO Equalization via In-Context Learning
item.description: In this work, we demonstrate that ICL can be also used to tackle the problem of multi-user equalization in cell-free MIMO systems with limited fronthaul capacity.

item.title: DepthMOT: Depth Cues Lead to a Strong Multi-Object Tracker
item.description: Inspired by this, even though the bounding boxes of objects are close on the camera plane, we can differentiate them in the depth dimension, thereby establishing a 3D perception of the objects.

item.title: Have You Merged My Model? On The Robustness of Large Language Model IP Protection Methods Against Model Merging
item.description: Model merging is a promising lightweight model empowerment technique that does not rely on expensive computing devices (e. g., GPUs) or require the collection of specific training data.

item.title: SpeechAlign: Aligning Speech Generation to Human Preferences
item.description: However, the integration of human feedback to align speech outputs to human preferences is often neglected.

item.title: LGSDF: Continual Global Learning of Signed Distance Fields Aided by Local Updating
item.description: Implicit reconstruction of ESDF (Euclidean Signed Distance Field) involves training a neural network to regress the signed distance from any point to the nearest obstacle, which has the advantages of lightweight storage and continuous querying.

item.title: HSViT: Horizontally Scalable Vision Transformer
item.description: While the Vision Transformer (ViT) architecture gains prominence in computer vision and attracts significant attention from multimedia communities, its deficiency in prior knowledge (inductive bias) regarding shift, scale, and rotational invariance necessitates pre-training on large-scale datasets.

item.title: AutoCodeRover: Autonomous Program Improvement
item.description: Recent progress in Large Language Models (LLMs) has significantly impacted the development process, where developers can use LLM-based programming assistants to achieve automated coding.

item.title: NAF-DPM: A Nonlinear Activation-Free Diffusion Probabilistic Model for Document Enhancement
item.description: Real-world documents may suffer various forms of degradation, often resulting in lower accuracy in optical character recognition (OCR) systems.

item.title: Exploring Quantization and Mapping Synergy in Hardware-Aware Deep Neural Network Accelerators
item.description: Energy efficiency and memory footprint of a convolutional neural network (CNN) implemented on a CNN inference accelerator depend on many factors, including a weight quantization strategy (i. e., data types and bit-widths) and mapping (i. e., placement and scheduling of DNN elementary operations on hardware units of the accelerator).

item.title: Retrieval-Augmented Open-Vocabulary Object Detection
item.description: Specifically, RALF consists of two modules: Retrieval Augmented Losses (RAL) and Retrieval-Augmented visual Features (RAF).

item.title: Evaluating Mathematical Reasoning Beyond Accuracy
item.description: To measure reasoning beyond final-answer accuracy, we introduce ReasonEval, a new methodology for evaluating the quality of reasoning steps.

item.title: Better Monocular 3D Detectors with LiDAR from the Past
item.description: Accurate 3D object detection is crucial to autonomous driving.

item.title: MealRec$^+$: A Meal Recommendation Dataset with Meal-Course Affiliation for Personalization and Healthiness
item.description: Due to constraints related to user health privacy and meal scenario characteristics, the collection of data that includes both meal-course affiliation and two levels of interactions is impeded.

item.title: ATFNet: Adaptive Time-Frequency Ensembled Network for Long-term Time Series Forecasting
item.description: To capitalize on both of these strengths, we propose ATFNet, an innovative framework that combines a time domain module and a frequency domain module to concurrently capture local and global dependencies in time series data.

item.title: SafetyPrompts: a Systematic Review of Open Datasets for Evaluating and Improving Large Language Model Safety
item.description: Researchers and practitioners have met these concerns by introducing an abundance of new datasets for evaluating and improving LLM safety.

item.title: GloSoFarID: Global multispectral dataset for Solar Farm IDentification in satellite imagery
item.description: Solar Photovoltaic (PV) technology is increasingly recognized as a pivotal solution in the global pursuit of clean and renewable energy.

item.title: Multi-Task Learning for Features Extraction in Financial Annual Reports
item.description: For assessing various performance indicators of companies, the focus is shifting from strictly financial (quantitative) publicly disclosed information to qualitative (textual) information.

item.title: HOEG: A New Approach for Object-Centric Predictive Process Monitoring
item.description: To leverage this enriched data, we propose the Heterogeneous Object Event Graph encoding (HOEG), which integrates events and objects into a graph structure with diverse node types.

item.title: Class Similarity Transition: Decoupling Class Similarities and Imbalance from Generalized Few-shot Segmentation
item.description: This paper focuses on the relevance between base and novel classes, and improves GFSS in two aspects: 1) mining the similarity between base and novel classes to promote the learning of novel classes, and 2) mitigating the class imbalance issue caused by the volume difference between the support set and the training set.

item.title: Flexible Fairness Learning via Inverse Conditional Permutation
item.description: Equalized odds, as a popular notion of algorithmic fairness, aims to ensure that sensitive variables, such as race and gender, do not unfairly influence the algorithm prediction when conditioning on the true outcome.

item.title: Rethinking the Spatial Inconsistency in Classifier-Free Diffusion Guidance
item.description: Classifier-Free Guidance (CFG) has been widely used in text-to-image diffusion models, where the CFG scale is introduced to control the strength of text guidance on the whole image space.

item.title: Chinese Sequence Labeling with Semi-Supervised Boundary-Aware Language Model Pre-training
item.description: Experimental results on Chinese sequence labeling datasets demonstrate that the improved BABERT variant outperforms the vanilla version, not only on these tasks but also more broadly across a range of Chinese natural language understanding tasks.

item.title: Multi-agent Long-term 3D Human Pose Forecasting via Interaction-aware Trajectory Conditioning
item.description: Our model effectively handles the multi-modality of human motion and the complexity of long-term multi-agent interactions, improving performance in complex environments.

item.title: Iterative Refinement Strategy for Automated Data Labeling: Facial Landmark Diagnosis in Medical Imaging
item.description: Automated data labeling techniques are crucial for accelerating the development of deep learning models, particularly in complex medical imaging applications.

item.title: LayoutLLM: Layout Instruction Tuning with Large Language Models for Document Understanding
item.description: The core of LayoutLLM is a layout instruction tuning strategy, which is specially designed to enhance the comprehension and utilization of document layouts.

item.title: Tree Search-Based Policy Optimization under Stochastic Execution Delay
item.description: We show that given observed delay values, it is sufficient to perform a policy search in the class of Markov policies in order to reach optimal performance, thus extending the deterministic fixed delay case.

item.title: Taming Transformers for Realistic Lidar Point Cloud Generation
item.description: Diffusion Models (DMs) have achieved State-Of-The-Art (SOTA) results in the Lidar point cloud generation task, benefiting from their stable training and iterative refinement during sampling.

item.title: TIM: A Time Interval Machine for Audio-Visual Action Recognition
item.description: We address the interplay between the two modalities in long videos by explicitly modelling the temporal extents of audio and visual events.

item.title: ITA-ECBS: A Bounded-Suboptimal Algorithm for Combined Target-Assignment and Path-Finding Problem
item.description: Multi-Agent Path Finding (MAPF), i. e., finding collision-free paths for multiple robots, plays a critical role in many applications.

item.title: Robust Data Pruning: Uncovering and Overcoming Implicit Bias
item.description: However, little is known about its impact on classification bias of the trained models.

item.title: Deep Optics for Video Snapshot Compressive Imaging
item.description: We believe this is a milestone for real-world video SCI.

item.title: David and Goliath: An Empirical Evaluation of Attacks and Defenses for QNNs at the Deep Edge
item.description: To fill this gap, we empirically evaluate the effectiveness of attacks and defenses from (full-precision) ANNs on (constrained) QNNs.

item.title: Fighting crime with Transformers: Empirical analysis of address parsing methods in payment data
item.description: With the emergence of Transformers and Generative Large Language Models (LLM), we explore the performance of state-of-the-art solutions given the constraint of processing a vast amount of daily data.

item.title: Spatio-Temporal Attention and Gaussian Processes for Personalized Video Gaze Estimation
item.description: Additionally, our approach integrates Gaussian processes to include individual-specific traits, facilitating the personalization of our model with just a few labeled samples.

item.title: MindSet: Vision. A toolbox for testing DNNs on key psychological experiments
item.description: Multiple benchmarks have been developed to assess the alignment between deep neural networks (DNNs) and human vision.

item.title: How to Evaluate Entity Resolution Systems: An Entity-Centric Framework with Application to Inventor Name Disambiguation
item.description: These benchmark data sets can then be used for model training and a variety of evaluation tasks.

item.title: Language Models on a Diet: Cost-Efficient Development of Encoders for Closely-Related Languages via Additional Pretraining
item.description: The world of language models is going through turbulent times, better and ever larger models are coming out at an unprecedented speed.

item.title: Detecting Every Object from Events
item.description: Object detection is critical in autonomous driving, and it is more practical yet challenging to localize objects of unknown categories: an endeavour known as Class-Agnostic Object Detection (CAOD).

item.title: Automated discovery of symbolic laws governing skill acquisition from naturally occurring data
item.description: Skill acquisition is a key area of research in cognitive psychology as it encompasses multiple psychological processes.

item.title: Technical Report: The Graph Spectral Token -- Enhancing Graph Transformers with Spectral Information
item.description: Graph Transformers have emerged as a powerful alternative to Message-Passing Graph Neural Networks (MP-GNNs) to address limitations such as over-squashing of information exchange.

item.title: Rethinking Diffusion Model for Multi-Contrast MRI Super-Resolution
item.description: Recently, diffusion models (DM) have been applied in magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) super-resolution (SR) reconstruction, exhibiting impressive performance, especially with regard to detailed reconstruction.

item.title: Data Stream Sampling with Fuzzy Task Boundaries and Noisy Labels
item.description: In the realm of continual learning, the presence of noisy labels within data streams represents a notable obstacle to model reliability and fairness.

item.title: Camera-Based Remote Physiology Sensing for Hundreds of Subjects Across Skin Tones
item.description: Remote photoplethysmography (rPPG) emerges as a promising method for non-invasive, convenient measurement of vital signs, utilizing the widespread presence of cameras.

item.title: Tensorized Ant Colony Optimization for GPU Acceleration
item.description: For the tensorization of ant system, we propose a preprocessing method to reduce the computational overhead by calculating the probability transition matrix.
